    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi, \n\nTrying to call `ioctl` via Luajit ffi fails on master, where it worked on previous versions.\nI did `git bisect` and it appears to be introduced by #38027.\n\nFor context, I'm using the ioctl to get the pixel size of the window to use with Kitty graphics protocol. \nI think this is a bug because reading the referenced commit, it seems it was only supposed to affect the server.\n\nMany thanks!\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean`\n- Paste the example below\n- `:%lua`\n- An error is shown.\n\n```\nlocal ffi = require(\"ffi\")\nffi.cdef([[\ntypedef struct {\n  unsigned short row;\n  unsigned short col;\n  unsigned short xpixel;\n  unsigned short ypixel;\n} winsize;\nint ioctl(int, int, ...);\n]])\n\nlocal TIOCGWINSZ = nil\nif vim.fn.has(\"linux\") == 1 then\n  TIOCGWINSZ = 0x5413\nelseif vim.fn.has(\"mac\") == 1 then\n  TIOCGWINSZ = 0x40087468\nelseif vim.fn.has(\"bsd\") == 1 then\n  TIOCGWINSZ = 0x40087468\nend\n\nlocal sz = ffi.new(\"winsize\")\nassert(ffi.C.ioctl(1, TIOCGWINSZ, sz) == 0, \"Failed to get terminal size\")\n\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe assertion should not produce an error.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nmaster\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty 0.45.0-4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from repo, as well as nightly nvim-linux-x86_64.tar.gz",
